                    },
                    "body": "This is actually due to how the Dojo Textarea dijit works; escaped text leads to breakage of the dijit.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-13T13:34:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-13T13:34:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/48431",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djungbluth",
                        "name": "djungbluth",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Jungbluth",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Okay, but I couldn't find out what actually \"breaks\". Can you briefly elaborate on this, please?\r\n\r\nThat something like the following is possible, is really fatal in my opinion:\r\n\r\n$dojoForm->addElement('Textarea', 'name', array('value'=>'<script>alert('Boo!');<\/script>'));\r\n\r\nOne could use the SimpleTextarea view helper which does escaping by default but I like the dynamic resizing feature of the \"full\" Textarea. Or, one could filter the input, etc... What would be best practice?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=djungbluth",
                        "name": "djungbluth",
                        "displayName": "Daniel Jungbluth",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-09-14T19:53:24.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-09-14T19:53:24.000+0000"
                }
            ]
